OL,7,FMr Price said that Betteridge claimed
OL,8,Fthat he acted in self-defence during
OL,9,Fthe incident, and stated it was
OL,10,Fsomething he regretted but "had to do
OL,11,Fas he believed it to be necessary to
OL,12,Fdefend himself".
OL,14,FHe added: "It's to be noted that the
OL,15,Ffirst thing that Mr Betteridge had
OL,16,Fdone after the killing was to brag
OL,17,Fabout it and the next thing he did in
OL,18,Fless than three minutes was to try and
OL,19,Fchange his appearance."
